\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ajv1665702717885.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ajv1665702717885.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ajv1665702717885.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ajv1665702717885\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify a range of ports that the exclusive server will listen on when using a TCP or TLS connection.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__topic_d139022e1_d139023e1_d139024e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__p_d139025e1_d139026e1_d139027e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/gates=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PortFrom</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PortTo</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__section_w3376ab1b5b3_w3377ab1b5_w3378ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__d6632e17\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__d6632e20\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PRE_START]\nTCP:+13002|user|P@55word|server2</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section pre\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__section_w3379ab1b5b5_w3380ab1b5_w3381ab1\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[SERVERS]\nsales = userver.exe /ex /gates=3800-4010</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__section_dng_fxv_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1026814e82\">Arguments </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__p_d139034e1_d139035e1_d139036e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PortFrom</var> and <var class=\"keyword varname\">PortTo</var>—decimal port numbers.\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">PortFrom</var> must be less than <var class=\"keyword varname\">PortTo</var>, but no other\n        checks are performed.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__section_vhx_gxv_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1026814e103\">Use </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__p_d139040e1_d139041e1_d139042e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/gates</span> switch can only be used\n        for an exclusive connection to a server (started using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ex</span> command\n        line switch). In effect, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/gates</span> turns off connection inheritance. For\n        more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"csd1665702527989.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/csd1665702527989.html\" title=\"When a client application needs to connect to a Uniface Server, it does so via a Uniface Router, which makes the required physical connections from the client to the Uniface Server. The client may have multiple logical connections and each logical connection may pass over several physical connections.\">Logical and Physical Connections</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__section_tk5_3xv_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1026814e129\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__p_d139046e1_d139047e1_d139048e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/gates</span> switch in a UST\n        declaration to specify a range of ports to be searched by the Uniface Router when it\n        attempts to start an exclusive server using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ex</span>. For example, on a mobile\n        device that periodically goes out of range of the server, you should use\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/gates</span> to ensure that it can re-establish the connection with the same\n        exclusive server.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__p_d139049e1_d139050e1_d139051e1\">If port number are incorrectly specified, the errors\n        are reported in the Uniface Router’s log file, and no connection is made. If a port cannot\n        be found in the specified range, an error is reported to the client.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ajv1665702717885__p_d139052e1_d139053e1_d139054e1\">If an exclusive Uniface Server is killed or crashes,\n        the recovery behavior depends on whether inheritance was used or whether the server has its\n        own listening port. </p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bja1665703273342.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/ex</a><p>Starts the UST as an exclusive Uniface Server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yah1705913880881.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Exclusive Server Failure Recovery</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525728\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525728\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/gates Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specify a range of ports that the exclusive server will listen on when using a TCP or TLS connection. /gates= PortFrom - PortTo For example: [PRE_START] TCP:+13002|user|P@55word|server2 Copy [SERVERS] sales = userver.exe /ex /gates=3800-4010 Copy Arguments PortFrom and PortTo —decimal port numbers. PortFrom must be less than PortTo , but no other checks are performed. Use The /gates switch can only be used for an exclusive connection to a server (started using the /ex command line switch). In effect, /gates turns off connection inheritance. For more information, see Logical and Physical Connections . Description Use the /gates switch in a UST declaration to specify a range of ports to be searched by the Uniface Router when it attempts to start an exclusive server using /ex . For example, on a mobile device that periodically goes out of range of the server, you should use /gates to ensure that it can re-establish the connection with the same exclusive server. If port number are incorrectly specified, the errors are reported in the Uniface Router’s log file, and no connection is made. If a port cannot be found in the specified range, an error is reported to the client. If an exclusive Uniface Server is killed or crashes, the recovery behavior depends on whether inheritance was used or whether the server has its own listening port. Related Links /ex Starts the UST as an exclusive Uniface Server. Exclusive Server Failure Recovery Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}